# Code Decomposition and File Size Rules

These rules enforce readable, maintainable file sizes and clear separation of concerns.

---

## File Size Limits

| Category | Max lines | Action when exceeded |
|---|---|---|
| React component file | 300 | Extract sub-components or hooks |
| Custom hook file | 200 | Split into focused hooks |
| Utility / helper file | 150 | Split by domain |
| Type definitions file | 200 | Split by domain |
| IPC handler group (Electron) | 200 | Split by feature |
| Electron main entry | 100 | Delegate to modules |

Before creating or modifying a file, check its current line count. If your change would push it beyond the limit, refactor first.

---

## Separation of Concerns

**One concern per file:**
- A component file renders UI and delegates logic to hooks.
- A hook file manages state, effects, or derived data.
- A utility file exports pure functions with no side effects.
- A types file exports only types and interfaces.
- An action registry file exports named action functions.

**Extraction triggers:**
- Inline handler exceeding ~15 lines: extract to named function or hook.
- JSX block exceeding ~50 lines with self-contained logic: extract to sub-component.
- 3+ `useState`/`useEffect` hooks serving the same feature: extract to custom hook.
- Utility function used by 2+ files: extract to shared utility module.

---

## Naming Conventions

| Type | Pattern | Example |
|---|---|---|
| React component | PascalCase `.tsx` | `DesktopProgressDock.tsx` |
| Custom hook | `use-` prefix, kebab-case `.ts` | `use-folder-actions.ts` |
| Utility module | kebab-case `.ts` | `label-formatters.ts` |
| Types file | kebab-case `.ts` | `viewer-types.ts` |
| Action registry | kebab-case `.ts` | `viewer-actions.ts` |
| Constants | kebab-case `.ts` | `ui-text.ts` |
| Test file | `*.test.ts` or `*.test.tsx` | `label-formatters.test.ts` |

